Which of the following best describes a valid use of the groupdel command?
A)  You may force group deletion with the - f option.
B)  If a users primary group is to be deleted, that user must be deleted first or have theirprimary group changed.
C)  Groupdel can be run at any time, regardless of group membership.
D)  The - r option for groupdel will recursively change users GIDs after group deletion.
B
B. The groupdel command cannot delete groups unless there are no users who have thegiven group as their primary GID. Therefore, option B best fits the scenario. There is no - for - r option, making options A and D incorrect.
